The following example:
{code}
class U {
  def f[T](x:T):T=x
}
object H extends Application {
  val u=new U
  val z:Int=(u.f _)(4)
  println("done")
}
{code}
results in:
{code}
java.lang.NoSuchMethodError: H$$$$anonfun$$1.apply(I)I
{code}

Replacing {{u.f}} with {{u.f[Int]}} works ok; possibly related are SI-1317 and SI-1570.
